==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: White-tie
<hw>White-tie</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>requiring formal
evening clothes, usually interpreted as a white bow tie and a tailcoat
for men, and a formal evening dress for women; -- <as>as, a
<ex>white-tie</ex> reception at the embassy</as>. Contrasting with
<contr>black-tie</contr> and <contr>informal</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Whitetop</ent>⟦br⟧
